==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Optigraph
<hw>Op"ti*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Optic</ets>
+ <ets>-graph</ets>: cf. F. <ets>opticographe</ets>. See <er>Optic</er>,
<pos>a.</pos> ]</ety> <def>A telescope with a diagonal eyepiece,
suspended vertically in gimbals by the object end beneath a fixed
diagonal plane mirror. It is used for delineating landscapes, by means
of a pencil at the eye end which leaves the delineation on
paper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Optimacy</ent>⟦br⟧
